1)  Description of the Main Target Image

There are actually two separate “towers” in the scene:

• Left‐Hand Tower (“red‐green‐yellow stack”):  
  – It is built as a vertical sandwich of six pieces in five layers.  
  – Top and bottom are the same red block (each has a large circular cut‐out).  
  – Between those red blocks are two narrow green rectangular blocks and, in the very middle, what appears as a yellow “circle” from the front—but is in fact made by placing two yellow half‐cylinders side by side.  
  – Hence the layer order from bottom to top is:  
     1) Red circular‐cut block  
     2) Green rectangular block  
     3) Two yellow half‐cylinders side by side   
     4) Green rectangular block  
     5) Red circular‐cut block  

• Right‐Hand Tower (“orange & blue rocket”):  
  – A tall orange cylinder stands in the center.  
  – Around its lower half is a ring of three small blue rectangular blocks.  
  – Leaning outward at the base are three identical orange wedges (forming a tripod shape).  
  – Sitting on the very top of the cylinder is a single orange wedge (or “roof” piece) placed point‐up.  
  – Altogether this “rocket” uses eight pieces:
     • 1 Orange cylinder  
     • 3 Small blue rectangular blocks (forming the ring)  
     • 3 Orange wedges for the base  
     • 1 Orange wedge on top  

2)  Selection of Required Blocks (by Dictionary Index)

Matching each shape/color/orientation exactly (no re‐orienting allowed), the needed blocks are:

• Left‐Hand Tower:  
  – Red blocks with circular hole: index 3  
  – Green horizontal rectangular blocks: index 6  
  – Yellow half‐cylinders (horizontal): index 10  

  Specifically:  
  – 2 × Block 3 (one for top, one for bottom)  
  – 2 × Block 6 (the two green “bands”)  
  – 2 × Block 10 (the two yellow half‐cylinders in the middle)  

• Right‐Hand Tower:  
  – Orange cylinder (vertical): index 9  
  – Blue rectangular blocks (horizontal): index 4  
  – Orange wedges at base (leaning outward): index 16  
  – Orange wedge on top (point‐up): index 12  

  Specifically:  
  – 1 × Block 9  
  – 3 × Block 4  
  – 3 × Block 16  
  – 1 × Block 12  

3)  Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order

Below is one possible build sequence showing which block index to place at each step:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 3   (place bottom red circular‐cut)  
  Step2:  Move block with index 6   (first green rectangle above it)  
  Step3:  Move block with index 10  (first yellow half‐cylinder)  
  Step4:  Move block with index 10  (second yellow half‐cylinder, side by side)  
  Step5:  Move block with index 6   (second green rectangle above the yellows)  
  Step6:  Move block with index 3   (top red circular‐cut)  

  -- Now the right‐hand “rocket”: --

  Step7:  Move block with index 9   (orange cylinder, standing vertically)  
  Step8:  Move block with index 16  (first orange wedge at base)  
  Step9:  Move block with index 16  (second orange wedge at base)  
  Step10: Move block with index 16  (third orange wedge at base)  
  Step11: Move block with index 4   (first small blue block around cylinder)  
  Step12: Move block with index 4   (second small blue block around cylinder)  
  Step13: Move block with index 4   (third small blue block around cylinder)  
  Step14: Move block with index 12  (orange wedge on top as a “roof”)  
}
